    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nif i copy to system clipboard (wl-copy) with `:set clipboard=unnamedplus`\nwhen i close neovim it leaves a process behind\n\nthis process interferes with vim.pack, making it reinstall stuff not in\nmy config anymore after i comment their vim.pack.add line out and delete ~/.local/share/nvim\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n0a. downloaded the nvim v0.12 appimage, make executable, `alias nvim='path/to/appimage'`\n0b. monitor with `watch 'pgrep -a nvim'\n1. `nvim --clean` watch shows 3 processes\n2. `:checkhealth vim.provider` shows \"OK: Clipboard tool found: wl-copy\"\n   wl-copy --version is wl-clipboard 2.3.0\n3. :q!\n4. `:bd` `iasdf<esc>dd` `:q!`\n5. watch shows all nvim processes terminated\n6. `nvim --clean`\n7. `:set clipboard=unnamedplus`\n8. `iasdf<esc>dd` `:q!`\n9. watch shows one remaining process\n10. `pkill nvim`\n\nnow the vim.pack issue:\ncreate a config as follows in ~/.config/nvim\n1. init.lua containing:\n  ```lua\n  vim.o.clipboard = \"unnamedplus\"\n  require('user')\n  ```\n2. lua/user/init.lua containing:\n  ```lua\n  vim.pack.add({'https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig'})\n  ```\n3. `pkill nvim` and make sure to delete ~/.config/nvim/nvim-pack-lock.json and ~/.local/share/nvim\n4. `nvim ~/.config/nvim/init.lua`\n5. yes, install package, then `:q` \n6. watch shows all processes terminate\n7. `nvim ~/.config/nvim/init.lua`, then comment the require and copy something: `ji--<space><esc>x:x<cr>`\n8. watch shows lingering process, dont pkill\n9. remove `~/.local/share/nvim`\n10. `nvim ~/.config/nvim/init.lua`, then `:lua vim.pack.get()` prompts you to install plugin again\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n- make sure lingering processes are terminated in a reasonable amount of time\n- when starting a new nvim instance, prioritize the actual config at this point in time. i am not sure exactly what happened, but have 2 suspicions: a) it somehow remembers the cached require('user') call and that is still relevant, or b) due to the lingering process the vim.pack lockfile still contains active=true for the package and thus when it does not find it in ~/.local/share/nvim tries to reinstall it\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nappimage: NVIM v0.12.0 Build type: Release LuaJIT 2.1.1774638290\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno?\n\n### Operating system/version\n\narchlinux, kde\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\n`foot tmux -u` foot version: 1.26.1 +pgo +ime +graphemes +toplevel-tag +blur -assertions; tmux version: 3.6a;\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage, called via bash alias, i still have arch linux's package (version v0.11.7) in PATH",
