            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> You need to use :h vim.pack.del() to delete plugins installed with :h vim.pack.add(). If you don't, the lock file won't get updated and Neovim may try to install the package again\n\ni expected it to read my config only and just when i vim.pack.add, it looks at the lockfile whether a wanted version is already known.\n\n@justinmk yes, it is similar, however what bothered me more was, that it caused my config to be unpredictable, which is why i opened this issue.\n\nin fact, if this is the intended behaviour, it's a real bother, because i now cannot simply comment out a require, but have to read this file, find out if it installed any plugins and manually remove them. this makes editing the config bothersome and forgets the version of the plugin which i tested. if they pushed a breaking change ill have to deal with it immediately when i uncomment the require",
